cs.DL, cs.IR, cs.SI, cs.CY, cs.CR 

The paper discusses the differences between international and non-international scientific publication media, which is relevant to several sub-categories in computer science. The focus on bibliometric indicators and research quality suggests a connection to digital libraries (cs.DL) and information retrieval (cs.IR). The investigation of publication data at team and author level could also be relevant to social informatics (cs.SI) and cybernetics (cs.CY). Finally, the analysis of publication categories could relate to cryptography (cs.CR), which often involves international collaboration and publication.
